ENTRY       EC 6.2.1.39                 Enzyme
NAME        [butirosin acyl-carrier protein]---L-glutamate ligase;
            [BtrI acyl-carrier protein]---L-glutamate ligase;
            BtrJ
CLASS       Ligases;
            Forming carbon-sulfur bonds;
            Acid-thiol ligases
SYSNAME     [BtrI acyl-carrier protein]:L-glutamate ligase (ADP-forming)
REACTION    (1) ATP + L-glutamate + BtrI acyl-carrier protein = ADP + phosphate + L-glutamyl-[BtrI acyl-carrier protein] [RN:R08905];
            (2) ATP + L-glutamate + 4-amino butanoyl-[BtrI acyl-carrier protein] = ADP + phosphate + 4-(gamma-L-glutamylamino)butanoyl-[BtrI acyl-carrier protein] [RN:R08906]
ALL_REAC    R08905 R08906
SUBSTRATE   ATP [CPD:C00002];
            L-glutamate [CPD:C00025];
            BtrI acyl-carrier protein;
            4-amino butanoyl-[BtrI acyl-carrier protein]
PRODUCT     ADP [CPD:C00008];
            phosphate [CPD:C00009];
            L-glutamyl-[BtrI acyl-carrier protein];
            4-(gamma-L-glutamylamino)butanoyl-[BtrI acyl-carrier protein]
COMMENT     Catalyses two steps in the biosynthesis of the side chain of the aminoglycoside antibiotics of the butirosin family. The enzyme adds one molecule of L-glutamate to a dedicated acyl-carrier protein, and following decarboxylation of the product by EC 4.1.1.95, L-glutamyl-[BtrI acyl-carrier protein] decarboxylase, adds a second L-glutamate molecule.
            Requires Mg2+ or Mn2+, and activity is enhanced in the presence of Mn2+.
HISTORY     EC 6.2.1.39 created 2012
